leadership-approach|results_process_people_vision|balanced|results|process|people|vision|How the pattern moves between Results, Process, People, and Vision|The pattern may have several usable entry points. Results may appear first, but context can quickly call for Process, People, or Vision without making the response inconsistent.|This shows up when the situation contains several kinds of leadership demand at once. The useful skill is naming which need is current rather than moving between them silently.|It protects flexibility across outcome and follow-through, structure and standards, trust and shared commitment, and direction and future consequence. It needs a clear current priority so others can follow the shift.|active|leadership-approach::results_process_people_vision::balanced
