leadership-approach|process_results_vision_people|concentrated|process|results|vision|people|How Process organises the response|Process is likely to organise the first response by setting a clear sequence, standards, responsibilities, and a dependable way of working. Results and Vision add useful checks, while People may need deliberate attention before the response becomes too narrow.|This shows up when pressure makes order, repeatability, and reduced rework feel like the clearest way to begin. The next signals test whether the work also has a clear outcome and a decision people can act on, a wider direction and a reason for the choice being made, and communication, confidence, and shared commitment.|It protects the work from confusion, uneven standards, avoidable rework, and messy handovers. The main range to add is clearer communication, inclusion, and relational judgement, especially when the first response has already created movement.|active|leadership-approach::process_results_vision_people::concentrated
