leadership-approach|vision_people_process_results|balanced|vision|people|process|results|How the pattern moves between Vision, People, Process, and Results|The pattern may have several usable entry points. Vision may appear first, but context can quickly call for People, Process, or Results without making the response inconsistent.|This shows up when the situation contains several kinds of leadership demand at once. The useful skill is naming which need is current rather than moving between them silently.|It protects flexibility across direction and future consequence, trust and shared commitment, structure and standards, and outcome and follow-through. It needs a clear current priority so others can follow the shift.|active|leadership-approach::vision_people_process_results::balanced
leadership-approach|people_results_process_vision|concentrated|people|results|process|vision|How People organises the response|People is likely to organise the first response by checking trust, communication, inclusion, and what people need in order to move with the work. Results and Process add useful checks, while Vision may need deliberate attention before the response becomes too narrow.|This shows up when pressure makes trust, shared understanding, and commitment feel like the clearest way to begin. The next signals test whether the work also has a clear outcome and a decision people can act on, usable structure and a sequence people can trust, and a wider direction and a reason for the choice being made.|It protects the work from low trust, weak buy-in, poor communication, and people being left behind by the pace of work. The main range to add is a stronger future frame, meaning, and possibility, especially when the first response has already created movement.|active|leadership-approach::people_results_process_vision::concentrated
